content:
In Salesforce Classic, use the features of the Case Feed email action to save time when writing messages and customize emails sent to customers. 

Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions.

To send emails:

* Send Email permission is required.
* The email action is available only if your organization uses Email-to-Case and Enable Case Feed Actions and Feed Items are enabled.
 
Click Email in the case feed. To write a reply to a message, click Reply or Reply All below an email message in the feed.

If using email templates, choose one for your message. Select a From address.

The email address of the contact who created the case automatically appears in the To field. Add more recipients by looking up an address or typing/pasting email addresses/names in the To field.

When you enter an email address or name that matches one contact/user, the address appears as a button with the person's name. Add several addresses at once by copying and pasting them separated by spaces or commas.

Edit the subject if desired. Use the rich text editor to add formatting to your message.

Create your message. If using quick text messages, type ;; to insert one. Save a copy of your message as a draft if enabled by your administrator.

Click Attach File or drag files in the attachments pane to add files to the message. Optionally, attach an article to the message.

Click Send Email.
title: Send and Reply to Email in Service Cloud
